Data Preparation

Data

Read in the data for the Oxford Utilitarianism Scale (ous):

ous <- read.csv("../Data/data_preprocessed.csv")

Inclusion and Exclusion Criteria

Finalized data exclusion rules:

  1. did not finish the survey (completed in preprocessing);
  2. provided incorrect answers to three careless responding checks;
  3. found the survey materials confusing;
  4. had technical problems while completing the survey; or
  5. did not fill out the survey in their self-reported native language
# Exclusionary criteria
ous <-
  ous %>% 
  # Did not complete survey (completed in previous step)
  # Provided correct answers to careless question checks
  filter(careless_1 == 2) %>% 
  filter(careless_2 == 2) %>% 
  filter(careless_3 == 1) %>% 
  # Did not find materials confusing after responding
  filter(!is.na(confusion)) %>% 
  filter(confusion < 3) %>% 
  # Did not have technical problems while completing the survey
  filter(technical_problems == 1) %>% 
  # Filled out survey in their self-reported native language
  filter(native_language == 1) 

# Filter languages
ous <-
  ous %>%
  filter(
    Q_Lang == "EN" |
      Q_Lang == "ZH-S" |
      Q_Lang == "FR" |
      Q_Lang == "DE" |
      Q_Lang == "EL" |

# combine spanish
ous$Q_Lang <-

Plot prep function

Each plot will have the following: 1) Appended sample sizes to the language name 2) Reliabilities shown in descending order by translated/untranslated 3) Saved to 6.875 x 9 inches size as a .png file

plot_prep <- function (alpha_df) {
  alpha_df_plot <- alpha_df
  alpha_df_plot <- mutate(alpha_df_plot, language = as.character(language))
  for (h in 1:nrow(alpha_df_plot)) {
    alpha_df_plot[h, "language"] = paste(alpha_df_plot[h, "language"], " (", alpha_df_plot[h, "n"], ")", sep = "")
  }
  alpha_df_plot <- mutate(alpha_df_plot, language = fct_reorder(language, reliability, .desc = FALSE))
  return(alpha_df_plot)
}

Reliability Analysis

For each scale, we calculated alpha/omega and 95% confidence intervals for each subscale in each language.

We then created the plots based on the language-wise reliabilities.

Reliability for each language

# IB alpha
for (i in 1:nrow(IB_alpha_df)) {
  dat <- filter(ous_IB, Q_Lang == IB_alpha_df[i, "language"])[, 1:5]
  alpha <- 
    ci.reliability(data = dat,
               type = "alpha",
               interval.type = "bca",
               B = 6500,
               conf.level = 0.95)
  IB_alpha_df[i, "reliability"] = alpha$est
  IB_alpha_df[i, "lower"] = alpha$ci.lower
  IB_alpha_df[i, "upper"] = alpha$ci.upper
}

# IB omega
for (i in 1:nrow(IB_omega_df)) {
  dat <- filter(ous_IB, Q_Lang == IB_omega_df[i, "language"])[, 1:5]
  omega <- 
    ci.reliability(data = dat,
               type = "omega",
               interval.type = "bca",
               B = 6500,
               conf.level = 0.95)
  IB_omega_df[i, "reliability"] = omega$est
  IB_omega_df[i, "lower"] = omega$ci.lower
  IB_omega_df[i, "upper"] = omega$ci.upper
}

# IH alpha
for (i in 1:nrow(IH_alpha_df)) {
  dat <- filter(ous_IH, Q_Lang == IH_alpha_df[i, "language"])[, 1:4]
  alpha <- 
    ci.reliability(data = dat,
               type = "alpha",
               interval.type = "bca",
               B = 6500,
               conf.level = 0.95)
  IH_alpha_df[i, "reliability"] = alpha$est
  IH_alpha_df[i, "lower"] = alpha$ci.lower
  IH_alpha_df[i, "upper"] = alpha$ci.upper
}

# IH omega
for (i in 1:nrow(IH_omega_df)) {
  dat <- filter(ous_IH, Q_Lang == IH_omega_df[i, "language"])[, 1:4]
  omega <- 
    ci.reliability(data = dat,
               type = "omega",
               interval.type = "bca",
               B = 6500,
               conf.level = 0.95)
  IH_omega_df[i, "reliability"] = omega$est
  IH_omega_df[i, "lower"] = omega$ci.lower
  IH_omega_df[i, "upper"] = omega$ci.upper
}

Combine data frames

IB_df <- rbind(
  IB_alpha_df,
  IB_omega_df
)

IB_df$omega <- as.factor(IB_df$omega)

IH_df <- rbind(
  IH_alpha_df,
  IH_omega_df
)

IH_df$omega <- as.factor(IH_df$omega)

Reliability plot

Create and save plot:

IB_plot <- ggplot(data = plot_prep(IB_df), aes(x = reorder(language, as.numeric(omega)), y = reliability)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = omega), stat = "identity", position = position_dodge(width = 0.75), size = 2) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = lower, ymax = upper), position = position_dodge(width = 0.75), width = 0.75, size = 0.75) +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0, 0)) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0, 1)) +
  expand_limits(y = c(0.25, 1)) +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        panel.background = element_blank(), axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
        plot.margin = margin(r = 10),
        text = element_text(family = "sans", size = 5),
        axis.title.x = element_text(size = 15),
        legend.title = element_blank(),
        legend.key = element_rect(fill = NA),
        legend.text = element_text(size = 12),
        legend.position = c(0.17, 0.96),
        legend.key.size = unit(0.15, "cm"),
        legend.box.background = element_rect(colour = "black", size = 1.5),
        axis.title.y = element_text(size = 15),
        axis.text.x = element_text(colour = "black", size = 12.5),
        axis.text.y = element_text(colour = "black", size = 10),
        plot.title = element_text(size = 10, face = "bold", colour = "white"),
        axis.line.x = element_line(color="black", size = 1),
        axis.line.y = element_line(color="black", size = 1),
        axis.ticks = element_line(colour = "black", size = 1),
        axis.ticks.length = unit(0.1, "in")) +
  xlab("Language") +
  ylab("Reliability") +
  ggtitle("xxx") + 
  guides(color = guide_legend(reverse = TRUE)) +
  scale_color_hue(labels = c("Alpha", "Omega")) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = c(0.80), size = 1, linetype = "dotted", color = "grey25") +
  coord_flip()
